Use ASP.NET Core's `WebApplicationFactory<TEntryPoint>` — it hosts your app in-memory and gives you an `HttpClient` without opening a real port.

**Pattern:**

```csharp
public class McpIntegrationTests : IClassFixture<WebApplicationFactory<Program>>
{
    private readonly WebApplicationFactory<Program> _factory;

    public McpIntegrationTests(WebApplicationFactory<Program> factory)
    {
        _factory = factory;
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task Initialize_ReturnsCapabilities()
    {
        var client = _factory.CreateClient();

        // Send MCP initialize request
        var request = new
        {
            jsonrpc = "2.0",
            id = 1,
            method = "initialize",
            @params = new
            {
                protocolVersion = "2025-03-26",
                capabilities = new { },
                clientInfo = new { name = "test-client", version = "1.0" }
            }
        };

        var response = await client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", request);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();

        var result = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<JsonElement>();
        Assert.Equal("2.0", result.GetProperty("jsonrpc").GetString());
        Assert.True(result.TryGetProperty("result", out var res));
        Assert.True(res.TryGetProperty("capabilities", out _));
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **No real port** — `WebApplicationFactory` uses an in-memory `TestServer`
- **Full pipeline** — middleware, routing, DI all run normally
- **SSE/Streamable HTTP** — for streaming endpoints, use `HttpCompletionOption.ResponseHeadersRead` and read the stream line-by-line
- **Customize DI** — override `WithWebHostBuilder` to swap dependencies (e.g., mock tool handlers)

For SSE streaming responses:

```csharp
var response = await client.SendAsync(request,
    HttpCompletionOption.ResponseHeadersRead);
using var stream = await response.Content.ReadAsStreamAsync();
using var reader = new StreamReader(stream);
var line = await reader.ReadLineAsync(); // read SSE events
```

Add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing` to your test project to get `WebApplicationFactory`.
